===Etymology===
It is shaped like corn or wheat (similar to [[禾]]), symbolizing the coming of the crops. Its ancient sound begins with "ml-".<!--citation needed; in which period of Chinese history did it have this pronunciation--> The meaning "come" was originally represented by [[麥]], adding a radical meaning "footprint" or "walk slowly". Their meanings have interchanged. M-remaining is 麥, l-remaining is 來.

